const faqs = [
  {
    q: "My Manitowoc Easy-Read display shows an error code. Can you read it?",
    a: "Yes. Manitowoc Easy-Read display codes are well-documented and we have the Manitowoc service manual references. Common codes (E1 water inlet, E2 harvest sensor, E3 control board, plus others) we know directly. Reading correctly equals targeted repair instead of trial-and-error parts swapping."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Indigo NXT IY, IB, and ID?",
    a: "Three size tiers. IY is large modular (450 to 1,200 lb/day) for high-volume operations. IB is mid-size (420 to 620 lb/day) for mid-volume restaurants and cafés. ID is compact undercounter (320 to 520 lb/day) for bars and small operations. All use the same architecture and diagnostic system; the differentiator is production capacity."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Manitowoc Indigo NXT IY-0454A, IY-0696A, IB-0420A, ID-0322A?",
    a: "Yes. These are our most common Manitowoc service calls. Common parts (water inlet valves, harvest sensors, condenser fan motors) on the van."
  },
  {
    q: "What's AlphaSan and LuminIce II?",
    a: "AlphaSan is silver-ion antimicrobial protection built into water-contact surfaces (slows biological growth on the evaporator and water lines). LuminIce II is a UV light system that kills airborne contaminants in the storage bin. Both reduce but don't eliminate cleaning service: Manitowoc still requires 2 to 4 cleanings per year. Both require periodic maintenance (UV bulb replacement every 1 to 2 years on heavy-use units)."
  },
  {
    q: "My Manitowoc is 10 years old and needs major repair. Worth fixing?",
    a: "Usually yes. A 10-year Indigo NXT cabinet is typically excellent; components fail but the cabinet does not. Replacement equivalent runs $5,500 to $12,000 depending on size. Component repair on the existing cabinet runs $1,400 to $2,800 typical. Math usually favors repair for a properly-maintained Manitowoc."
  },
  {
    q: "Manitowoc Ice vs Manitowoc Cranes: same company?",
    a: "No, common confusion. Manitowoc Ice is part of Welbilt Inc. (commercial foodservice equipment). Manitowoc Cranes is a separate company entirely (industrial cranes). Both originated from the same Wisconsin-based parent decades ago but have been corporately split. We service Manitowoc Ice machines. We don't service cranes."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty. Manitowoc component warranties processed separately through Welbilt service network. BHGS #A49573 and BBB A+."
  }
];

