<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Manitowoc service</p>
    <h2>The industry workhorse of commercial ice machines.</h2>

    <p>Manitowoc Ice is the industry workhorse of commercial ice machines in the US market. Wisconsin-based, manufactured since 1964. Now part of Welbilt Inc. (private equity-owned by Apollo Global Management since 2017), but still Wisconsin-based with continuous American manufacturing heritage.</p>

    <p>Manitowoc dominates the chain restaurant and hotel segment of commercial ice. The <strong>Indigo NXT</strong> flagship line (IY series large modular, IB mid-size, ID compact undercounter) is the standard at Marriott, Hilton, and Hyatt corporate hotel kitchens, plus chain restaurant operations. The sophisticated diagnostic system (Easy-Read display, AlphaSan antimicrobial, LuminIce II growth inhibitor with UV light) makes Manitowoc a service-friendly brand.</p>

    <p>We service the entire Manitowoc lineup across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>Indigo NXT IY series</strong> large modular (IY-0454A, IY-0524A, IY-0606A, IY-0696A, IY-0906A, IY-1196A, sizes by lb/day production). <strong>IB series</strong> mid-size (IB-0420A, IB-0520A, IB-0620A). <strong>ID series</strong> compact undercounter (ID-0322A, ID-0452A, ID-0522A). <strong>IRT series</strong> remote-condensed. <strong>R-Series nugget</strong> (RNS-0385A, RNS-0820A) for hospitality nugget ice. <strong>Q-Series</strong> legacy machines still in service.</p>

    <p>EPA 608 Universal plus R-290 certified (post-2020 Indigo NXT models transitioning to R-290 hydrocarbon refrigerant). BHGS #A49573. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608 Universal (#1346255700410) verifiable.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Series-aware diagnosis</p>
    <h2>The Manitowoc lineup, and what fails on each tier.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Manitowoc uses a clear size-tier framework across the Indigo NXT line, plus the R-Series nugget architecture and Q-Series legacy machines still in active service. Diagnostics differ by tier and ice format.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Indigo NXT IY Series (Large Modular)</h3>
    <p>The flagship Manitowoc line. IY-0454A (450 lb/day air-cooled, the most popular IY size), IY-0524A (525 lb/day), IY-0606A (600 lb/day), IY-0696A (700 lb/day), IY-0906A (900 lb/day), IY-1196A (1,200 lb/day). Air-cooled (-A), water-cooled (W), remote-condensed (R). Common in chain hotels, large restaurants, and hospitals.</p>
    <p>Common Indigo NXT IY failures:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Scale buildup on vertical evaporator plate.</strong> Manitowoc uses a vertical evaporator architecture (different from Hoshizaki cell-and-curtain). AlphaSan antimicrobial protection slows biological growth but doesn't prevent calcium scale.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve diaphragm.</strong> Year 5 to 8 typical failure window.</li>
      <li><strong>Hot gas valve (Acu-Thaw harvest cycle).</strong> Harvest cycle release issues.</li>
      <li><strong>Harvest sensor drift.</strong> Cycles ending too early or too late, affecting ice quality.</li>
      <li><strong>LuminIce II UV light bulb.</strong> UV bulb life is roughly 10,000 to 15,000 hours; replacement needed periodically (1 to 2 years on heavy-use units).</li>
      <li><strong>Easy-Read display fault codes.</strong> Read correctly first for targeted repair.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Indigo NXT IB Series (Mid-Size)</h3>
    <p>IB-0420A (420 lb/day), IB-0520A (520 lb/day), IB-0620A (620 lb/day). Common in mid-size restaurants, cafés, and smaller hotels. Same Indigo NXT architecture, smaller production capacity.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Indigo NXT ID Series (Compact Undercounter)</h3>
    <p>ID-0322A (320 lb/day undercounter), ID-0452A (450 lb/day), ID-0522A (520 lb/day). Common in bars, cafés, and small operations where compact form factor matters.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">IRT Remote-Condensed</h3>
    <p>Indigo NXT with remote condenser on the roof. Higher capacity, no kitchen heat impact. Premium installations. Service requires understanding of remote-condensed line set work and refrigerant-circuit length compensation.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">R-Series Nugget Ice</h3>
    <p>RNS-0385A (385 lb/day nugget), RNS-0820A (820 lb/day). Hospitality, healthcare, and premium beverage applications. Different architecture from cube: auger-driven mechanism with separate gear reducer wear pattern.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Q-Series (Legacy)</h3>
    <p>Pre-Indigo NXT models still in active service. Parts available through the Welbilt network for several more years. We service these.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top Manitowoc repairs we see in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on Manitowoc service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Cleaning service.</strong> AlphaSan plus LuminIce II reduce but don't eliminate cleaning. Standard 2 to 4 times per year. $200 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve replacement.</strong> Common 5 to 8 year failure.</li>
      <li><strong>Easy-Read display diagnostic plus targeted repair.</strong> Read codes, repair specific component. Manitowoc is service-friendly because of this.</li>
      <li><strong>Hot gas valve (Acu-Thaw).</strong> Harvest cycle issues.</li>
      <li><strong>Harvest sensor replacement.</strong> Affects harvest timing and ice quality.</li>
      <li><strong>LuminIce II UV bulb replacement.</strong> Periodic, every 1 to 2 years on heavy-use units.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerant leak repair.</strong> EPA 608 leak repair before recharge. Post-2020 R-290 systems require R-290 certification.</li>
      <li><strong>Condenser fan motor (-A air-cooled).</strong> Typical 4 to 7 year coastal life.</li>
      <li><strong>Auger gear reducer (R-Series nugget).</strong> Mechanical wear, 6 to 9 year typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Compressor replacement (10 to 13 year units).</strong> Replace-vs-replacement decision based on cabinet condition.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five Manitowoc jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marriott hotel in West Hollywood · Manitowoc Indigo NXT IY-0454A air-cooled cube + 400 lb bin (6 years, R-404A)</h3>
        <p>Friday 8 PM, ice production stopped. Tech dispatched 25 minutes from West Hollywood branch. Easy-Read display showed scale-buildup notification. Drained, applied Manitowoc Cleen Ice cleaner (brand-spec), ran cleaning cycle, sanitized, replaced water filter. Production restored. Total: $120 plus $280 cleaning plus $160 filter = $560. Hotel facilities manager appreciated brand-spec cleaner usage and Easy-Read documentation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Chain restaurant in Beverly Hills · Manitowoc Indigo NXT IB-0520A mid-size cube (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Refrigerant slow leak, machine needed top-off every 6 months. EPA 608 leak detection with electronic detector: small leak at evaporator brazed joint. Pumped down, brazed repair, evacuated to 500 microns, recharged R-404A. Now compliant with EPA 608. Total: $120 plus $480 refrigerant plus $720 labor plus leak detection = $1,420.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bar in Pasadena · Manitowoc Indigo NXT ID-0322A undercounter cube (7 years)</h3>
        <p>Easy-Read display "E1" error code (water inlet fault). Diagnosed: water inlet valve diaphragm degraded. Replaced inlet valve. Cleared error code. Total: $120 plus $290 part plus 1.5 hours = $410.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hospital cafeteria in Pasadena · Manitowoc R-Series RNS-0385A nugget ice (9 years)</h3>
        <p>Auger noise, nugget production reduced. Diagnosed: auger gear reducer wear (typical 6 to 9 year). Replaced gear reducer. Nugget production restored. Total: $120 plus $640 part plus 2.5 hours = $1,000.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hilton hotel in Santa Monica · Manitowoc Indigo NXT IY-0696A large cube (10 years)</h3>
        <p>Multiple Easy-Read error codes simultaneously. Diagnosed: control board end-of-life plus LuminIce II UV bulb burned out (cascading at 10 years). Replaced board plus UV bulb. Total: $120 plus $620 board plus $180 UV bulb plus 3 hours = $1,420. 5+ years more service life expected.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

